OL,3,CUnion members from Aslef to continue
OL,4,Ctrain strikes over the weekend
OL,6,FThe disruption comes as members of
OL,7,Fdrivers' union Aslef take part in an
OL,8,Fovertime ban from Thursday to
OL,9,FSaturday, and for 48 hours from Monday.
OL,11,FA spokesperson said: "ASLEF is the
OL,12,Fonly rail union continuing to strike,
OL,13,Ftargeting passengers and preventing
OL,14,Ftheir own members from voting on the
OL,15,Fpay offer that remains on the table.
