OL,3,CUnion members from Aslef to continue
OL,4,Ctrain strikes over the weekend
OL,6,FAslef general secretary, Mick Wheelan,
OL,7,Fsaid: "Our members voted
OL,8,Foverwhelmingly ` yet again ` for
OL,9,Fstrike action.
OL,11,F"Those votes show ` yet again ` a
OL,12,Fclear rejection by train drivers of
OL,13,Fthe ridiculous offer put to us in
OL,14,FApril last year by the Rail Delivery
OL,15,FGroup which knew that offer would be
OL,16,Frejected because a land grab for all
OL,17,Fthe terms & conditions we have
OL,18,Fnegotiated over the years would never
OL,19,Fbe accepted by our members."
